{# 
    Frameset (<frameset>)
    ===========================================================================

    Defines a set of frames.

    Variables:
    - `frameset_rows`: The number and size of rows in the frameset. Defaults to "100%,*".
    - `frameset_cols`: The number and size of columns in the frameset. Defaults to "100%,*".
    - `frameset_content`: The content (frames) to be included inside the frameset. Defaults to "Default frameset content".

    Notes:
    - The <frameset> element is deprecated in HTML5 and should not be used. Consider using CSS and JavaScript instead.
    - The `| e` filter is used to escape any special characters in the variables to prevent XSS attacks.

    Links:
    - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/frameset
    - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_frameset.asp

#}

<frameset 
    rows="{{ frameset_rows | default('100%,*') | e }}" 
    cols="{{ frameset_cols | default('100%,*') | e }}"
>
    {{ frameset_content | default('Default frameset content') | e }}
</frameset>
